smartsox_comments: The belt clasp/fastener was rather "stiff" and not as easy to use as I would have liked. I found that I needed to be careful not to pinch fingers. I have a pair of hiking pants with a similar belt that has a button on the front of the clasp that you push and the buckle is easily released.     The sensors on the right sock and belt were easy to plus into the charger wires at night. While the right sock has no covering over the sensor jack making it easy to plug in the charging wire, the left sock had a cloth covering over of the sensor that made plugging in the charging wire more difficult. The cloth covering was tight across the top and didn't yield very easily. I had to work at pushing back the tight covering directly over the sensor with one hand while positioning and pushing the wire into the monitor. I would suggest either leaving the covering off the monitor (similar to the right sock) or replacing the present covering with a material more easily pulled back off of the monitor. It's possible that over time the material would loosen up or tear away (which I suspect happened to the right sock).
